  "summary": "Jatinder Mehra, a distinguished figure in India’s steel industry with over six decades of experience, passed away, leaving behind a legacy of technical excellence and industrial leadership.",
  "content": "<h2>Introduction</h2><p>Jatinder Mehra, a stalwart of India’s steel industry with more than six decades of experience in the metals and manufacturing sector, passed away on Tuesday. He was widely respected for his technical expertise, leadership capabilities, and long-standing contribution to industrial growth in India.</p><p>His passing marks the loss of a prominent figure who played a significant role in shaping India’s steel production landscape.</p><h2>Career and Contributions</h2><p>Over his extensive career, Jatinder Mehra held senior leadership positions in various steel enterprises and was instrumental in advancing production efficiency and quality standards.</p><ul><li>Contributed to modernization of steel plants</li><li>Promoted adoption of advanced metallurgical techniques</li><li>Strengthened operational excellence frameworks</li></ul><p>His work supported the expansion of India’s steel manufacturing capacity.</p><h2>Role in India’s Industrial Growth</h2><p>The steel sector is a core industry that drives infrastructure development, automobile manufacturing, and construction activities.</p><ul><li>Foundation of infrastructure projects</li><li>Critical input for manufacturing sector</li><li>Supports economic growth and employment</li></ul><p>Leaders like Mehra contributed to strengthening India’s self-reliance in steel production.</p><h2>Industry Recognition</h2><ul><li>Respected technical mentor</li><li>Advisor in industrial modernization initiatives</li><li>Advocate for sustainable steel production practices</li></ul><p>His expertise influenced generations of engineers and managers in the metals sector.</p><h2>Legacy</h2><p>Jatinder Mehra is remembered for:</p><ul><li>Commitment to industrial innovation</li><li>Technical acumen in metallurgy</li><li>Integrity and professional excellence</li></ul><p>His career reflects the evolution of India’s steel industry over several decades.</p><h2>Conclusion</h2><p>The demise of Jatinder Mehra represents a significant loss to India’s industrial community. His contributions to the steel sector have left a lasting impact on infrastructure development and manufacturing growth in the country.</p><h2>Exam Perspective</h2><ul><li>Sector: Steel Industry</li><li>Theme: Industrial Development</li><li>Relevant for UPSC GS-III (Economy & Industry)</li></ul><h2>Sources</h2><p>Industry Reports 2026, Steel Sector Publications</p>",
